'\"macro stdmacro
.TH SMTVERS 1M
.SH NAME
smtvers \- shows SMT version of a FDDI station
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B smtvers 
.I host
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Smtvers
may be used to find out the SMT version(s) of the specified host.
The host can be a MAC address of a host or the symbolic name
of its MAC address which can be found in
.I /etc/ethers
or the NIS
.I ethers.byname
map.
.P
.I Smtvers
sends an illegal ECHO_REQUEST frame to the
host, and decodes the returned REQUEST_DENIED_FRAME (RDF)
in order to figure out the SMT version(s) the host supports.
Thus,
.I smtvers
may also be used as a tool to check if
the host's
SMT supports RDF or not.
.sp .5
Only the super-user may invoke
.IR smtvers .
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
If
.I smtvers
fails for any reason,
it prints an appropriate message on standard error and exits with
non-zero status.
.SH "FILES"
/etc/ethers	ethernet-address(MAC-address) database
.SH SEE ALSO
smtd(1M), fddi(7)
